only the first chapter finished but it has been pretty interesting so far
it is really selling an oppressive atmosphere so far
I feel that every time I finish a kyougoku novel I want to read something different, but when I actually do so I go "hm, kyougoku's writing is actually better" lmao

but also some stuff I didn't like that much, and also one youkai explanation that totally lost me (I need to reread that part)
in any case it is clearly just the first half of a whole so I'm reserving further judgement until I finish this
